Monitoring & Observability (Zabbix)

To centralize infrastructure visibility, I deployed a Linux-based Zabbix Server and configured monitoring across Windows and Linux hosts. This allows the lab to track host availability, system performance, service health, and network-related metrics from one platform.

<img width="2560" height="1315" alt="Zabbix dashboard showing host availability, alerts, and metrics" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/40324bfc-9aa0-4c1e-9f4c-1ca61a02cc75" />

Centralized Zabbix dashboard providing real-time visibility into host availability, system performance, alerts, and network-related metrics.

